title: House damaged in out-of-control grassfire at Diggers Rest
text:
House damaged in out-of-control grassfire at Diggers Rest Updated February 04, 2017 12:49:26 Map: Diggers Rest 3427 
A house has been damaged and others are under threat as an out-of-control grassfire burns on Melbourne's north-west fringe. 
The Country Fire Authority has called in more than 30 vehicles to help contain the blaze at Diggers Rest, which broke out on a private property. 
Air support has also been called in to assist. 
A watch and act message has been issued for Bulla and Diggers Rest. 
The fire is burning in a southerly direction near the Bulla-Diggers Rest Road towards the Calder Freeway. 
Smoke may be visible from nearby communities and roads, the CFA said.
